### 2.3 Data Flow Architecture

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[React Frontend] -->|REST API| B[Express Backend]
    B -->|Mongoose| C[(MongoDB)]
    B -->|Typing Data| D[Python ML Script]
    D -->|Analysis Report| B
    B -->|Report + Prompt| E[Gemini API]
    E -->|AI Response| B
    B -->|Results| A
```

**Key Flow — Typing ML Pipeline:**
1. User types → keypress data captured in React
2. Session ends → data sent via API to Express → saved in MongoDB
3. User clicks "Run Analysis" → Express calls Python ML script with user's session data from MongoDB
4. ML script trains 3 models on user's data → returns `analysis_report` JSON
5. Report saved to MongoDB → displayed in frontend
6. User optionally clicks "Get AI Overview" → Express sends report to Gemini → response displayed

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Typing data is sent directly to the backend via API — **no JSON file downloads**. The ML model reads from MongoDB through the Express bridge.

